WEBVTT

00:09.843 --> 00:11.245
- * ONE, TWO, THREE, FOUR

00:11.279 --> 00:13.381
* ONE, TWO, THREE,
FOUR, FIVE, SIX *

00:13.414 --> 00:15.383
* SHAKE IT, DUDE

00:15.416 --> 00:23.357
*

00:32.300 --> 00:33.667
* ONE, TWO, THREE, FOUR

00:33.701 --> 00:38.572
*

00:42.343 --> 00:45.146
- * FOLLOW THAT DREAM

00:45.179 --> 00:47.481
* I GOTTA FOLLOW THAT DREAM

00:47.515 --> 00:49.083
* KEEP IT MOVING,
I'M MOVING ON *

00:49.117 --> 00:51.252
* KEEP IT MOVING

00:51.285 --> 00:52.686
* I'VE GOTTA FOLLOW THAT DREAM

00:52.720 --> 00:55.756
* WHEREVER THAT DREAM
MAY LEAD *

00:55.789 --> 00:57.625
* I GOTTA FOLLOW THAT DREAM

00:57.658 --> 01:01.162
- SINCE WHEN DID WOODY'S
BECOME A CUNT-RY CLUB?

01:01.195 --> 01:03.297
- SINCE YOU'RE HERE.
- HOW ABOUT ANOTHER ROUND?

01:03.331 --> 01:05.133
- AHH... NO.

01:05.166 --> 01:06.834
LAST CALL FOR YOU,
YOU HAVE SCHOOL TOMORROW.

01:06.867 --> 01:09.537
- YOUR FIRST DAY, I'M SO PROUD
OF YOU!

01:09.570 --> 01:11.172
- ONE MINUTE HE'S IN A COMA

01:11.205 --> 01:13.407
AND THE NEXT HE'S GOING
TO COLLEGE.

01:13.441 --> 01:14.608
- WELL, IN THE WORDS
OF THE KING,

01:14.642 --> 01:15.843
"YOU GOTTA FOLLOW THAT DREAM."

01:15.876 --> 01:19.580
- MM. NOW THERE'S A DREAM.

01:19.613 --> 01:21.582
YEE-HAW.

01:21.615 --> 01:23.817
- * WHEREVER THAT DREAM
MAY LEAD *

01:23.851 --> 01:26.187
- I'VE HAD THE SAME DREAM
EVER SINCE I'VE BEEN LITTLE:

01:26.220 --> 01:29.390
TO FALL IN LOVE, GET MARRIED,
AND HAVE A BABY.

01:29.423 --> 01:30.858
- WELL, TWO OUT OF THREE
AIN'T BAD.

01:30.891 --> 01:32.593
- THREE OUT OF THREE
IS EVEN BETTER.

01:32.626 --> 01:34.195
- YOU'RE GETTING MARRIED?

01:34.228 --> 01:35.296
- WHEN DID YOU DECIDE?

01:35.329 --> 01:36.130
- WHY DIDN'T YOU TELL US?

01:36.164 --> 01:38.699
- YES. A FEW WEEKS AGO.
WE JUST DID.

01:38.732 --> 01:40.768
- AAH!
[laughter]

01:40.801 --> 01:43.871
- HERE'S A TOAST
TO THE HAPPY COUPLE.

01:43.904 --> 01:45.873
MAY YOU COME TO YOUR SENSES
BEFORE IT'S...

01:45.906 --> 01:48.342
TOO LATE.

01:48.376 --> 01:49.743
- OH, THIS IS SO EXCITING!

01:49.777 --> 01:54.448
EVERYONE'S DREAMS
ARE COMING TRUE.

01:54.482 --> 01:56.417
HEY, WHAT'S YOUR DREAM,
SWEETIE?

01:56.450 --> 02:00.354
- MY DREAM IS TO ONE DAY KNOW
WHAT MY DREAM IS.

02:00.388 --> 02:02.423
- DREAMING'S FOR PEOPLE WHO LIKE
TO SLEEP.

02:02.456 --> 02:04.558
I'D RATHER BE AWAKE AND FUCKING.

02:04.592 --> 02:05.693
- I'M GOING
TO CALL TEDDY AND TELL HIM

02:05.726 --> 02:07.261
TO GET HIS ASS DOWN HERE.

02:07.295 --> 02:09.297
- AND I WAS HAVING
SUCH A GOOD TIME.

02:09.330 --> 02:11.299
- WOULD YOU
JUST FUCKING LAY OFF HIM?

02:11.332 --> 02:12.866
THE GUY'S BEEN REALLY DEPRESSED.

02:12.900 --> 02:14.868
- YEAH, HE'S BEEN TRYING TO FIND
A JOB EVER SINCE THAT INCIDENT.

02:14.902 --> 02:17.505
- I WOULDN'T EXACTLY CALL
SHOOTING A LOAD OFF

02:17.538 --> 02:20.474
IN FRONT OF MY BOSS
"AN INCIDENT."

02:20.508 --> 02:23.744
- HE'S NOT PICKING UP.

02:23.777 --> 02:26.814
- YOU DON'T SUPPOSE HE'D DO
SOMETHING...DRASTIC,

02:26.847 --> 02:28.249
DO YOU?
I-I MEAN,

02:28.282 --> 02:30.484
HE COULD BE LYING
IN BED RIGHT NOW...

02:30.518 --> 02:32.386
DEAD.

02:32.420 --> 02:33.854
- HOW COULD YOU TELL?

02:33.887 --> 02:34.922
- * KEEP IT MOVING

02:34.955 --> 02:36.290
* MOVING ON

02:36.324 --> 02:38.259
* KEEP IT MOVING
AND MOVING ON *

02:38.292 --> 02:39.827
* KEEP IT MOVING

02:39.860 --> 02:40.961
* AND MOVING ON

02:40.994 --> 02:42.363
* KEEP IT MOVING

02:42.396 --> 02:43.797
- TED?

02:43.831 --> 02:47.268
[keys jingling]

02:47.301 --> 02:50.338
[door opening]

02:50.371 --> 02:53.441
TEDDY?

03:07.721 --> 03:09.357
TED, WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

03:09.390 --> 03:10.958
- [gasps]

03:10.991 --> 03:11.959
WHAT THE HELL'S IT LOOK LIKE?

03:11.992 --> 03:15.829
- GOD...IT SMELLS
LIKE A BATH HOUSE IN HERE.

03:15.863 --> 03:18.832
WHEN IS THE LAST TIME
YOU LEFT THIS PLACE?

03:18.866 --> 03:20.901
- FOUR DAYS.

03:20.934 --> 03:22.503
I'M IN THE MIDDLE
OF A MARATHON.

03:22.536 --> 03:24.438
- JUST LIKE AMC.

03:24.472 --> 03:26.974
AMERICAN MASTURBATION CLASSICS.

03:27.007 --> 03:28.742
HONEY, I THINK YOU HAVE
A PROBLEM.

03:28.776 --> 03:30.210
- HUH. YOU'RE RIGHT.

03:30.244 --> 03:32.746
USUALLY RICKY ROD'S HAIRLESS
CHEW-HOLE DRIVES ME WILD.

03:32.780 --> 03:35.849
FOR SOME REASON
IT'S LOST ITS MAGIC.

03:35.883 --> 03:39.887
- I KNOW THAT YOU'VE BEEN
A LITTLE DEPRESSED LATELY,

03:39.920 --> 03:41.589
BUT YOU'VE GOT TO PULL YOURSELF
TOGETHER.

03:41.622 --> 03:43.691
- WHAT DO YOU THINK
I'M TRYING TO DO?

03:43.724 --> 03:44.858
ONLY YOU'RE NOT MAKING IT
ANY EASIER.

03:44.892 --> 03:47.795
IF YOU REALLY WANT TO HELP,
GRAB A NIPPLE AND SQUEEZE.

03:47.828 --> 03:49.530
- DO I LOOK
LIKE A HUMAN TIT CLAMP?

03:49.563 --> 03:52.333
- WHOA! LOOK AT THAT.

03:52.366 --> 03:53.867
OOH.

03:53.901 --> 03:55.669
- THAT IS HOT.

04:06.079 --> 04:07.848
UGH, NO!

04:07.881 --> 04:10.884
YOU ARE NOT SUCKING ME INTO
YOUR BLACK HOLE OF DEPRAVITY.

04:10.918 --> 04:14.688
NOW YOU GET UP,
YOU GET UP RIGHT NOW.

04:14.722 --> 04:16.590
- YOU'RE RIGHT.

04:16.624 --> 04:19.059
I'VE BEEN IN THIS BED
LONG ENOUGH.

04:19.092 --> 04:22.396
[groans]

04:26.667 --> 04:29.537
LET'S SEE WHO'S ON
DEMONDICK.COM, SHALL WE?

04:29.570 --> 04:32.606
- THAT IS NOT WHAT I MEANT.

04:32.640 --> 04:35.008
LISTEN TO ME, TEDDY.

04:35.042 --> 04:36.544
LOOK, I KNOW--

04:36.577 --> 04:39.847
I KNOW IT'S BEEN TOUGH
GETTING FIRED.

04:39.880 --> 04:43.351
IT'S--IT'S A TREMENDOUS BLOW.
- BLOW?

04:43.384 --> 04:44.685
- SCRATCH THAT.

04:44.718 --> 04:47.455
BUT--BUT THERE
IS A GREAT, BIG...

04:47.488 --> 04:50.057
FABULOUS WORLD OUT THERE.
- YEAH.

04:50.090 --> 04:51.692
LET ME TELL YOU SOMETHING

04:51.725 --> 04:53.561
ABOUT THAT GREAT, BIG,
FABULOUS WORLD OUT THERE.

04:53.594 --> 04:56.664
YOU EITHER JERK OFF
OR YOU GET JERKED OFF.

04:56.697 --> 04:58.899
[video chatter]

04:58.932 --> 05:03.036
YEAH! THAT'S IT.
GO FOR IT.

05:05.105 --> 05:08.075
- [moaning]

05:17.150 --> 05:19.753
[sighing]

05:21.955 --> 05:25.893
- AH...NO. NO.

05:25.926 --> 05:27.828
THAT WAS JUST FOR YOU.

05:27.861 --> 05:30.464
- SINCE WHEN DO YOU TURN DOWN
GETTING YOUR DICK SUCKED?

05:30.498 --> 05:31.865
- SINCE TOMORROW'S A BIG DAY.

05:31.899 --> 05:34.702
I NEED TO SAVE MY ENERGY
FOR MY ART.

05:34.735 --> 05:38.071
- WHAT DO YOU CALL THIS?

05:38.105 --> 05:40.107
- I PROMISE I'LL LET YOU BLOW ME
TOMORROW NIGHT.

05:40.140 --> 05:42.576
- YEAH? WELL, WHO SAYS I'LL BE
IN THE MOOD?

05:42.610 --> 05:44.077
- YOU'RE ALWAYS IN THE MOOD,

05:44.111 --> 05:46.547
WHICH IS KIND OF AMAZING
WHEN YOU THINK OF IT.

05:46.580 --> 05:48.849
I MEAN, AT YOUR AGE.

05:55.756 --> 05:58.592
[urinating]

06:08.902 --> 06:10.871
[toilet flushing]

06:17.645 --> 06:19.613
- DRAWING MY COCK AGAIN?

06:19.647 --> 06:21.915
- JUST DOODLING.

06:26.554 --> 06:28.155
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

06:28.188 --> 06:29.623
- I'M JUST DOODLING.

06:29.657 --> 06:31.792
- I TOLD YOU, I HAVE SCHOOL.

06:41.935 --> 06:43.971
- THINK I'D LOOK GOOD
WITH A NEW HAIRCUT?

06:44.004 --> 06:45.639
I THINK I WOULD.
DO YOU?

06:45.673 --> 06:47.207
- WHAT'D YOU HAVE IN MIND?

06:47.240 --> 06:49.076
- I DON'T KNOW.
MAYBE BUZZ IT ALL OFF

06:49.109 --> 06:50.611
OR BLEACH IT.

06:50.644 --> 06:55.148
- THAT'D BE COOL.
FOR TWO YEARS AGO.

06:55.182 --> 06:57.451
SO WHAT'S WRONG?

06:57.485 --> 06:59.787
- NOTHING'S WRONG. WHY DO YOU
THINK SOMETHING'S WRONG?

06:59.820 --> 07:01.689
- BECAUSE EVERY TIME
SOMETHING'S WRONG,

07:01.722 --> 07:03.023
YOU WANT TO CHANGE YOUR HAIR.

07:03.056 --> 07:05.092
- THAT IS SO NOT TRUE!

07:05.125 --> 07:07.961
- MICHAEL'S THINKING
ABOUT CHANGING HIS HAIR.

07:07.995 --> 07:10.798
- OH, GOD.

07:10.831 --> 07:15.536
BABY, WHAT'S WRONG?
TELL ME.

07:15.569 --> 07:16.604
- ALL RIGHT, ALL RIGHT.

07:16.637 --> 07:18.739
IT FEELS LIKE EVERYBODY'S LIFE
IS SPEEDING ALONG.

07:18.772 --> 07:20.140
LINDSAY AND MELANIE
ARE GETTING MARRIED,

07:20.173 --> 07:22.543
AND JUSTIN'S GOING
TO ART SCHOOL.

07:22.576 --> 07:23.777
HE WAS PRACTICALLY DEAD

07:23.811 --> 07:25.579
A COUPLE OF MONTHS AGO,
FOR FUCK'S SAKE.

07:25.613 --> 07:27.114
AND I'M STILL STUCK
AT THE STARTING GATE.

07:27.147 --> 07:29.116
- WELL, SINCE WHEN IS IT A RACE?

07:29.149 --> 07:31.084
- SINCE I FEEL
LIKE I'M COMING IN LAST.

07:31.118 --> 07:33.721
- WELL, THEN DO SOMETHING
ABOUT IT.

07:33.754 --> 07:36.023
AFTER ALL, YOU'RE CUTE.
YOU'RE YOUNG.

07:36.056 --> 07:37.491
YOU'RE HUNG.

07:37.525 --> 07:38.792
- LIKE WHAT?

07:38.826 --> 07:40.093
- QUIT THE FUCKING Q!

07:40.127 --> 07:42.896
- YOU DON'T THINK I'D LIKE TO?

07:42.930 --> 07:45.132
BUT I HAVE OBLIGATIONS
TO OTHERS.

07:45.165 --> 07:47.968
- WELL, AS ONE OF THE "OTHERS"
TO WHOM YOU ARE REFERRING,

07:48.001 --> 07:51.705
I WOULD SAY YOUR FIRST
OBLIGATION IS TO YOURSELF.

07:51.739 --> 07:55.609
SO WHAT WOULD MAKE YOU HAPPY?

08:01.081 --> 08:03.116
- SHOULD WE HUM THE THEME
FROM JEOPARDY?

08:03.150 --> 08:06.119
- FUCK YOU.
[alarm whistles]

08:06.153 --> 08:07.721
WHAT WOULD MAKE ME HAPPY
IS TO GET TO WORK ON TIME

08:07.755 --> 08:09.590
AND NOT CATCH SHIT FROM MY BOSS.

08:09.623 --> 08:11.525
- MM, THANK GOD YOU'RE HERE.

08:11.559 --> 08:13.126
- WHERE HAVE YOU BEEN?

08:13.160 --> 08:14.628
YOU DIDN'T COME HOME
LAST NIGHT.

08:14.662 --> 08:16.263
- SOMEBODY GOT LUCKY.

08:16.296 --> 08:19.099
- GOOD FOR HIM.
I SPENT THE NIGHT AT TED'S.

08:19.132 --> 08:21.702
YOU GUYS, HE IS
IN DEEP-SHIT TROUBLE.

08:21.735 --> 08:23.604
WE NEED TO HAVE
AN INTERVENTION.

08:23.637 --> 08:25.773
- BOOZE?
- CRYSTAL?

08:25.806 --> 08:30.010
- WHIPPING THE WILLY.

08:30.043 --> 08:31.612
- SCHMUCK.

08:31.645 --> 08:33.647
COULDN'T EVEN GET
A DECENT ADDICTION.

08:33.681 --> 08:35.683
[quirky music]

08:35.716 --> 08:38.652
[moaning]

08:46.994 --> 08:48.929
- SO CAN I GET YOU GUYS
ANYTHING?

08:48.962 --> 08:51.198
COFFEE? JUICE?

08:51.231 --> 08:52.833
POPPERS?

08:52.866 --> 08:54.301
- DON'T GET TOO CLOSE.

08:54.334 --> 08:59.072
HE MAY ASK YOU
TO SQUEEZE SOMETHING.

08:59.106 --> 09:00.708
- SO WHAT'S UP?

09:00.741 --> 09:02.676
- YOU, TEDDY.

09:02.710 --> 09:04.645
YOU HAVE A PROBLEM.

09:04.678 --> 09:06.914
THAT'S WHY I BROUGHT MICHAEL
AND BRIAN.

09:06.947 --> 09:08.048
WE'RE YOUR FRIENDS,

09:08.081 --> 09:09.049
WE CARE ABOUT YOU.

09:09.082 --> 09:10.784
WE'RE HERE TO HELP.

09:10.818 --> 09:14.154
- NOT TO WORRY.
I'VE GOT THE SITUATION IN HAND.

09:14.187 --> 09:16.123
- YEAH, WE CAN SEE THAT.

09:16.156 --> 09:19.927
- LOOK, I'VE BEEN
UNDER A LOT OF STRESS LATELY,

09:19.960 --> 09:22.095
AND I HAVE BEEN RELEASING
SOME TENSION, THAT'S ALL.

09:22.129 --> 09:23.797
- HEY, JUST REMEMBER...

09:23.831 --> 09:26.299
YOU HAVE SO MUCH TO GIVE,
SO MANY GIFTS.

09:26.333 --> 09:27.868
THERE'S A GREAT, BIG,
FABULOUS WORLD--

09:27.901 --> 09:32.205
- YEAH, I ALREADY TRIED THAT.

09:32.239 --> 09:33.607
- FUCK THIS.

09:33.641 --> 09:35.876
GET OFF YOUR ASS.
GO TAKE A SHOWER.

09:35.909 --> 09:36.977
YOU REEK.

09:37.010 --> 09:39.880
AND GO FIND A JOB.

09:39.913 --> 09:41.949
- WHAT I THINK
BRIAN'S TRYING TO SAY

09:41.982 --> 09:44.117
IN HIS OWN--
OWN CARING WAY

09:44.151 --> 09:47.220
IS YOU'RE HAVING
A SELF-ESTEEM CRISIS.

09:47.254 --> 09:50.223
OKAY?
BUT WE KNOW THAT YOU CAN BECOME

09:50.257 --> 09:54.127
A VALUABLE AND PRODUCTIVE MEMBER
OF SOCIETY AGAIN.

09:54.161 --> 09:58.899
SO ALLOW US TO LOVE YOU
UNTIL YOU CAN LOVE YOURSELF.

09:58.932 --> 10:00.968
- I THINK HE'S LOVED HIMSELF
PLENTY.

10:01.001 --> 10:05.138
- HEY, IT'S KINNEY.
PUT OLIVER ON.

10:05.172 --> 10:08.375
[water running]
OLLIE? IT'S BRIAN.

10:08.408 --> 10:12.680
ARE YOU STILL LOOKING
FOR A REPLACEMENT FOR MENDOZA?

10:12.713 --> 10:14.214
WELL, I JUST FOUND HIM.

10:14.247 --> 10:17.818
HIS NAME IS SCHMIDT.

10:17.851 --> 10:20.120
TED SCHMIDT.

10:20.153 --> 10:22.189
YEAH, HE'S A TOTAL DORK.

10:22.222 --> 10:27.895
- PERFECT.
I'LL SEE HIM AT 4:00.

10:27.928 --> 10:29.997
- HEY, WONDER-WHACKER!

10:30.030 --> 10:31.865
I JUST RAVED ABOUT YOU
TO OUR HEAD OF ACCOUNTING.

10:31.899 --> 10:34.134
YOU HAVE A MEETING
AT 4:00.

10:34.167 --> 10:37.037
DON'T FUCK IT UP.

10:37.070 --> 10:40.808
- DON'T WORRY,
I'M TOO SORE TO FUCK ANYTHING.

10:43.010 --> 10:45.378
- THAT'S GOOD.

10:50.751 --> 10:51.885
THAT'S EXCELLENT.

10:51.919 --> 10:53.286
- THANK YOU.

10:53.320 --> 10:55.155
- ALL RIGHT, CLASS.

10:55.188 --> 10:59.392
LET'S FOCUS ON THE MUSCULATURE
OF THE BACK AND THE BUTTOCKS.

11:06.333 --> 11:10.971
HMM.

11:11.004 --> 11:15.208
- OH, FUCK!

11:15.242 --> 11:16.409
- SOMETHING WRONG, MR. TAYLOR?

11:16.443 --> 11:19.980
- NO.
NOTHING.

11:36.897 --> 11:39.900
- HEY, WHERE HAVE YOU BEEN?

11:39.933 --> 11:42.435
- A FRIEND WAS IN TROUBLE.

11:42.469 --> 11:44.471
- ANDREW'S BEEN LOOKING FOR YOU.

11:44.504 --> 11:47.474
- NICE OF YOU TO JOIN US,
NOVOTNY.

11:47.507 --> 11:49.509
- SORRY, ANDREW.
IT COULDN'T BE HELPED.

11:49.542 --> 11:51.411
- MAYBE WALTZING IN
ANY TIME YOU PLEASED

11:51.444 --> 11:52.846
WAS OKAY
WHEN YOU WERE RUNNING THINGS,

11:52.880 --> 11:54.381
BUT I'M IN CHARGE NOW.

11:54.414 --> 11:56.884
- LOOK, I SAID I'M SORRY, OKAY?

11:56.917 --> 11:58.952
- HEY, TAKE IT EASY.

11:58.986 --> 12:00.220
I'M NOT TRYING
TO BUST YOUR BALLS.

12:00.253 --> 12:02.756
IT'S JUST THAT,
WITH ALL YOUR EXPERIENCE,

12:02.790 --> 12:05.125
THERE'S A LOT I DEPEND
ON YOU FOR.

12:07.861 --> 12:10.463
- THANKS.
- LIKE, SOME CHILD JUST THREW UP

12:10.497 --> 12:11.899
IN FRONT OF THE DAIRY CASE.

12:11.932 --> 12:16.837
WHO CAN CLEAN IT UP
BETTER THAN YOU?

12:16.870 --> 12:19.840
- ATTENTION, BIG Q SHOPPERS.

12:19.873 --> 12:22.943
- SURE, ANDREW.
RIGHT AWAY.

12:26.246 --> 12:28.348
- OH, WHAT A JERK!

12:28.381 --> 12:31.985
WHY DO YOU PUT UP WITH IT?

12:32.019 --> 12:34.988
- I'D BETTER GET A MOP.

12:43.296 --> 12:44.397
- [sighs]

12:44.431 --> 12:48.268
[door opens and shuts]

12:51.371 --> 12:54.007
- MR. TAYLOR?
- DEAN RYERSON.

12:56.043 --> 12:58.378
- PROFESSOR STANLEY TELLS ME
YOU WERE HAVING SOME TROUBLE

12:58.411 --> 13:00.881
TODAY IN LIFE CLASS.

13:00.914 --> 13:02.149
- I WASN'T HAVING ANY TROUBLE.

13:02.182 --> 13:04.117
- SHE SAID YOU LOST CONTROL
OF YOUR HAND.

13:04.151 --> 13:07.254
- [laughs]
JUST FOR A SECOND.

13:07.287 --> 13:08.455
IT WASN'T A BIG DEAL.

13:08.488 --> 13:10.824
- MR. TAYLOR,
IF YOU'RE HAVING A PROBLEM--

13:10.858 --> 13:13.126
- IT'S NOT A PROBLEM.
I TOLD YOU.

13:13.160 --> 13:16.897
IT JUST--
IT GETS A LITTLE TIRED.

13:16.930 --> 13:21.334
MY OCCUPATIONAL THERAPIST
SAYS THE STRENGTH WILL BE BACK.

13:21.368 --> 13:22.970
- MAY I?

13:23.003 --> 13:27.140
- IT'S NOT--
IT'S NOT FINISHED.

13:36.349 --> 13:39.586
- YOU'RE A VERY TALENTED
YOUNG MAN, JUSTIN.

13:39.619 --> 13:43.223
YOU WOULDN'T HAVE BEEN ADMITTED
TO I.F.A. IF YOU WEREN'T.

13:43.256 --> 13:44.591
BUT, AS YOU KNOW,

13:44.624 --> 13:49.096
THIS IS
A VERY STRENUOUS PROGRAM.

13:51.464 --> 13:54.868
I THINK YOU NEED
TO SERIOUSLY CONSIDER

13:54.902 --> 13:57.304
WHETHER YOU'RE ABLE
TO MEET THE REQUIREMENTS.

14:08.982 --> 14:13.186
[door opens and closes]

14:15.055 --> 14:17.524
[clatter]

14:24.932 --> 14:27.100
- HEY, LADY.

14:27.134 --> 14:30.103
[upbeat music]

14:30.137 --> 14:37.410
*

14:37.444 --> 14:40.347
- HI.

14:43.350 --> 14:44.651
- HEY, MICHAEL.

14:44.684 --> 14:47.087
HOW'S IT GOING, BUD?

14:47.120 --> 14:49.990
- BETTER NOW THAT I'M HERE.

14:50.023 --> 14:52.159
HEY, DID YOU ORDER
THAT OLD JUSTICE LEAGUE?

14:52.192 --> 14:53.360
- YEAH.

14:53.393 --> 14:54.995
BUT IT MIGHT NOT GET HERE
IN TIME.

14:55.028 --> 14:56.396
- IN TIME FOR WHAT?

14:56.429 --> 14:58.465
- END OF THE MONTH,
I'M TAKING OFF FOR FLORIDA.

14:58.498 --> 15:00.333
- YEAH?
WHEN YOU COMING BACK?

15:00.367 --> 15:03.503
- I'M NOT.

15:03.536 --> 15:06.639
I GOT SOME FRIENDS DOWN IN
ST. PETE, TELLING ME FOR YEARS

15:06.673 --> 15:09.076
TO GET THE HELL OUT OF THE SNOW,
SO I FINALLY DECIDED.

15:09.109 --> 15:12.012
I'M PACKING UP THE VAN,
AND I'M TAKING OFF.

15:12.045 --> 15:14.247
- WHAT ABOUT THE STORE?

15:14.281 --> 15:17.517
- CLOSING IT.
22 YEARS IS LONG ENOUGH.

15:17.550 --> 15:19.552
I'M GOING TO KICK BACK,

15:19.586 --> 15:22.622
SMOKE SOME WEED,
DO SOME FISHING.

15:22.655 --> 15:24.591
MAYBE I'LL START UP A BAND.

15:24.624 --> 15:26.493
IT'S ALWAYS BEEN
A DREAM OF MINE.

15:32.199 --> 15:34.434
- WELL, GOOD LUCK, BUZZY.

15:34.467 --> 15:37.971
- THANKS, MICHAEL.

15:44.477 --> 15:47.580
[dance music]

15:47.614 --> 15:55.522
*

15:55.555 --> 15:57.624
- * LET'S TAKE A RIDE

15:57.657 --> 15:59.726
* 'CAUSE WE ARE ON THE RISE

15:59.759 --> 16:02.395
* TONIGHT

16:02.429 --> 16:10.370
*

16:34.294 --> 16:36.029
- I JUST WANT YOU TO KNOW

16:36.063 --> 16:38.665
HOW VERY, VERY PROUD
I AM OF YOU.

16:38.698 --> 16:39.799
- FOR WHAT?

16:39.832 --> 16:42.802
- FOR KICKING YOUR ADDICTION,
FOR GETTING OUT OF BED.

16:42.835 --> 16:45.105
FOR DOING SOMETHING PRODUCTIVE.

16:45.138 --> 16:46.573
- LIKE SHARING A BUMP
AT BABYLON.

16:46.606 --> 16:49.576
- LIKE GETTING A NEW JOB.

16:49.609 --> 16:52.312
- THANKS TO MY,
DARE I SAY IT,

16:52.345 --> 16:54.247
GOOD FRIEND BRIAN.

16:54.281 --> 16:55.582
- DON'T SAY IT.

16:55.615 --> 16:57.150
- WELL, YOU MUST HAVE
REALLY IMPRESSED THEM.

16:57.184 --> 17:01.254
- OLIVER SAID YOU
WERE EXCRUCIATINGLY BORING.

17:01.288 --> 17:03.090
WHICH, APPARENTLY,
IS QUITE A BIG COMPLIMENT

17:03.123 --> 17:04.291
FOR AN ACCOUNTANT.

17:04.324 --> 17:06.526
- [laughs]
- OKAY, I KNOW

17:06.559 --> 17:07.660
I'M NOT YOUR FAVORITE PERSON.

17:07.694 --> 17:10.197
IN FACT,
OUT OF THE 6 BILLION PEOPLE

17:10.230 --> 17:11.731
IN THE WORLD,
I'M SURE I RANK SOMEWHERE

17:11.764 --> 17:14.767
BELOW THE POPULATIONS OF ZAMBIA
AND ZIMBABWE,

17:14.801 --> 17:17.637
BUT, IF THERE'S EVER ANY WAY
I CAN RETURN THE FAVOR...

17:17.670 --> 17:19.372
- THERE IS.

17:19.406 --> 17:23.076
IF YOU SEE ME AT LUNCH,
PRETEND LIKE YOU DON'T KNOW ME.

17:23.110 --> 17:25.612
- GOTCHA.
- ONE FOR MIKEY.

17:25.645 --> 17:27.514
- GET THAT SHIT AWAY FROM ME.

17:27.547 --> 17:30.450
- WHAT'S WITH YOU?
- NOTHING.

17:32.719 --> 17:35.555
BUZZY'S MOVING TO FLORIDA.

17:35.588 --> 17:37.724
EVEN FUCKING BUZZY
HAS A DREAM.

17:37.757 --> 17:39.426
- WHO'S FUCKING BUZZY?

17:39.459 --> 17:41.394
- NO ONE.
I'VE SEEN HIM.

17:41.428 --> 17:44.564
- HE OWNS A COMIC BOOK STORE.

17:44.597 --> 17:46.699
HONEY, AREN'T THERE
OTHER PLACES?

17:46.733 --> 17:48.101
- THAT'S MY PLACE.

17:48.135 --> 17:50.470
I'VE BEEN GOING THERE
SINCE I WAS TEN.

17:50.503 --> 17:58.378
*

18:15.695 --> 18:18.365
- HEY!

18:18.398 --> 18:20.833
- HEY, YOURSELF.

18:23.670 --> 18:26.273
WHY AREN'T YOU HOME PACKING
YOUR LUNCH BOX

18:26.306 --> 18:27.474
FOR SCHOOL TOMORROW?

18:27.507 --> 18:30.277
- I DON'T NEED TO.
I'M NOT GOING.

18:30.310 --> 18:32.212
- LET ME GUESS,

18:32.245 --> 18:34.747
YOU HEARD THEY'RE GOING TO MAKE
YOU DRAW VAGINAS.

18:34.781 --> 18:38.685
- I QUIT.

18:38.718 --> 18:40.820
- YOU WHAT?
- WHAT FOR?

18:40.853 --> 18:44.291
- WELL, I CAN'T DRAW ANYMORE,
SO...

18:44.324 --> 18:45.925
WHAT'S THE POINT
IN WASTING MY TIME

18:45.958 --> 18:47.760
WHEN I COULD BE HERE

18:47.794 --> 18:49.862
POPPING PILLS
AND DRINKING BEERS

18:49.896 --> 18:52.232
AND STICKING MY GIMP HAND

18:52.265 --> 18:54.501
DOWN GUYS' PANTS?

18:54.534 --> 18:55.768
DO YOU WANT TO DANCE?

18:55.802 --> 18:57.404
- FUCK, YEAH.

18:57.437 --> 18:59.572
- THAT WAS GOING TO BE
MY NEXT QUESTION.

18:59.606 --> 19:02.475
*

19:02.509 --> 19:06.913
- WHAT'S THAT ALL ABOUT?

19:06.946 --> 19:09.916
- IT'S PAIN MANAGEMENT.

19:09.949 --> 19:14.187
*

19:14.221 --> 19:17.290
- I CAN'T WAIT
FOR THIS DAY TO BE OVER.

19:17.324 --> 19:21.528
- THANK GOD
IT'S ONLY ONCE A YEAR.

19:21.561 --> 19:22.662
- "FUN FOR THE WHOLE FAMILY."

19:22.695 --> 19:23.896
MORE LIKE,
"HERE'S YOUR BALLOON, KID,

19:23.930 --> 19:25.398
NOW SHUT UP AND LET ME SHOP!"

19:25.432 --> 19:26.833
- [laughs]

19:26.866 --> 19:29.536
- SO WHO'S THE VICTIM THIS YEAR?
- SALLY, THE NEW CASHIER.

19:29.569 --> 19:33.340
- SHE'S SWEET.
AT LEAST SHE WAS UNTIL TODAY.

19:33.373 --> 19:36.643
TODAY WE DRAIN HER OF HER SOUL,
HER DIGNITY.

19:36.676 --> 19:38.945
- SALLY JUST CALLED.
SHE'S NOT FEELING WELL.

19:38.978 --> 19:40.547
DID SOMEBODY TELL HER?

19:40.580 --> 19:42.982
- NOT ME.
- DIDN'T SAY A WORD.

19:43.015 --> 19:45.552
- WE NEED SOMEBODY ELSE.
IT'S ALL YOURS, NOVOTNY.

19:45.585 --> 19:47.720
- WAIT A MINUTE...
- STORE POLICY,

19:47.754 --> 19:49.722
THE NEWEST EMPLOYEE
GETS THE HONOR.

19:49.756 --> 19:51.658
- BUT MICHAEL'S
BEEN HERE FOREVER.

19:51.691 --> 19:53.826
- CORRECTION: HE LEFT,
THEN HE CAME BACK.

19:53.860 --> 19:55.828
SO, ACCORDING
TO MY CALCULATIONS, YOU'RE IT.

19:55.862 --> 19:57.464
NOW GO GET DRESSED.

19:57.497 --> 19:58.965
- FORGET IT!

19:58.998 --> 20:00.500
[balloon pops]

20:00.533 --> 20:05.705
[indistinct chatter]

20:05.738 --> 20:07.607
- CAN I HAVE A BALLOON,
PLEASE?

20:11.811 --> 20:13.012
BUT I WANTED A RED ONE.

20:13.045 --> 20:14.447
- LIFE SUCKS, KID.

20:14.481 --> 20:15.548
- LET'S GO, JIMMY.

20:15.582 --> 20:19.286
- BETTER YOU KNOW IT NOW
THAN BE DISAPPOINTED LATER.

20:19.319 --> 20:21.654
- I COULD SWEAR THAT'S MICHAEL.
- WHERE?

20:21.688 --> 20:23.890
- THERE, THE GUY
IN THE CLOWN SUIT.

20:23.923 --> 20:26.259
- WHAT WOULD HE BE DOING
IN A CLOWN SUIT?

20:26.293 --> 20:28.461
HE'S A MANAGER.
THEY DON'T MAKE MANAGERS CLOWNS.

20:28.495 --> 20:31.431
- EXCUSE ME,

20:31.464 --> 20:34.601
COULD WE GET A BALLOON
FOR OUR SON?

20:34.634 --> 20:36.269
- OH, THANKS,
BUT WE ONLY NEED ONE.

20:36.303 --> 20:38.271
- WE'RE LOOKING FOR OUR FRIEND
MICHAEL NOVOTNY.

20:38.305 --> 20:42.742
HE WORKS HERE.

20:42.775 --> 20:44.977
MICHAEL, IT IS YOU!

20:45.011 --> 20:45.845
- HONK, HONK.

20:45.878 --> 20:48.848
- OH, MICHAEL,
WHY ARE YOU DOING THIS?

20:48.881 --> 20:52.018
- DON'T ASK. AND DON'T TELL.
ESPECIALLY BRIAN.

20:52.051 --> 20:53.520
- THERE HAVE BEEN
SOME GREAT CLOWNS.

20:53.553 --> 20:55.822
BOZO, EMMETT KELLY.

21:00.026 --> 21:03.663
- WELL, HEY,
WHAT ABOUT GUS' BALLOON?

21:03.696 --> 21:05.498
- STILL WINS, ALWAYS.

21:05.532 --> 21:06.633
- HEY, GUYS, HOW'S IT GOING?

21:06.666 --> 21:08.535
- WHO'S THAT?

21:08.568 --> 21:11.304
- WHO, THE GEEZER?
FUCK IF I KNOW.

21:11.338 --> 21:13.573
OKAY, SHEP.
WE'RE READY TO BE WOWED.

21:13.606 --> 21:14.841
WHAT'S GOING TO MAKE US SELL
OUR BLOOD

21:14.874 --> 21:17.310
AND BUY
EASTON HEIGHTS TEA BAGS?

21:17.344 --> 21:18.611
- NO PRESSURE, HUH, BRI?

21:18.645 --> 21:20.747
- IF YOU'RE NOT FEELING
PRESSURE,

21:20.780 --> 21:24.951
I'M NOT DOING MY JOB.

21:24.984 --> 21:26.653
THAT'S INTERESTING.

21:26.686 --> 21:28.921
- UH, OF COURSE IT STILL NEEDS
SOME REFINING.

21:28.955 --> 21:32.359
I CAN GIVE YOU A POPPY
IN THERE LIKE THAT,

21:32.392 --> 21:33.393
AND, UH...

21:33.426 --> 21:34.994
STEMS.
WE NEED SOME GREEN STEMS.

21:35.027 --> 21:37.864
I'LL GIVE YOU SOME OF THAT.

21:37.897 --> 21:40.400
THERE YOU GO.

21:40.433 --> 21:41.934
AND YOU DON'T LIKE THE HEADER,
I'LL GIVE YOU A NEW HEADER.

21:41.968 --> 21:44.103
TRY THAT.

21:44.136 --> 21:45.938
- THAT'S AMAZING.
- THANKS.

21:45.972 --> 21:48.408
- I'M TALKING ABOUT THIS THING.

21:48.441 --> 21:53.346
- OH, STATE OF THE ART.
GO AHEAD, TRY IT.

22:01.588 --> 22:02.922
- ARE YOU FAMILIAR

22:02.955 --> 22:05.124
WITH THE PEACHTREE SOFTWARE?

22:05.157 --> 22:06.759
- IT'S JUST LIKE MY LAST JOB.

22:06.793 --> 22:08.361
- WE KEEP
OUR RECEIVABLES CURRENT,

22:08.395 --> 22:09.862
AND WE HAVE A REVOLVING LINE
OF CREDIT

22:09.896 --> 22:11.498
AT THE BANK OF PITTSBURGH.

22:11.531 --> 22:13.433
- JUST LIKE MY LAST JOB.

22:13.466 --> 22:15.568
- WE PAD OUR CLIENT BILLING.

22:15.602 --> 22:17.069
- JUST LIKE MY LAST JOB.

22:17.103 --> 22:20.106
- AND WE WALK AROUND
LIKE WE'RE DEAD INSIDE.

22:20.139 --> 22:22.709
- JUST LIKE MY LAST JOB.

22:22.742 --> 22:27.547
- MR. SCHMIDT?
MR. SCHMIDT?

22:27.580 --> 22:31.718
- I WILL GET STARTED ON THIS
RIGHT AWAY, MR. WERTSCHAFTER,

22:31.751 --> 22:33.119
UH...FLEISCHAFTER...

22:33.152 --> 22:36.689
MR. FLEI--
FLEISCHACKER.

22:36.723 --> 22:38.858
SIR...SHACKTER.

22:38.891 --> 22:42.695
[cell phone rings]

22:42.729 --> 22:43.996
TED SCHMIDT.

22:44.030 --> 22:47.133
- HEY, I JUST CALLED
TO SEE HOW IT'S GOING.

22:47.166 --> 22:48.968
- OH, IT'S GREAT.
COULDN'T BE BETTER.

22:49.001 --> 22:50.403
- SO WHAT'S IT LIKE?

22:50.437 --> 22:51.337
- GLORIOUS.

22:51.370 --> 22:54.474
I HAVE A DESK AND A CHAIR
AND A COMPUTER.

22:54.507 --> 22:56.409
- WHAT'S THE COLOR SCHEME?

22:56.443 --> 22:58.545
- BEIGEY-GRAY.

22:58.578 --> 23:00.012
OR GRAYISH-BEIGE.

23:00.046 --> 23:01.614
YOU KNOW, TAKE YOUR PICK.

23:01.648 --> 23:04.951
- WELL, THAT SOUNDS PERFECT,
HONEY.

23:04.984 --> 23:06.052
ALL RIGHT, WELL, JUST--

23:06.085 --> 23:08.054
JUST STAY OFF YOU-KNOW-WHAT.COM.

23:08.087 --> 23:10.590
[chuckles]

23:10.623 --> 23:15.027
THANK YOU, GOD,
FOR MAKING ME BAD AT MATH.

23:15.061 --> 23:17.764
HEY, YOU KNOW, YOU LOOK GOOD
WITH A LITTLE MAKEUP.

23:17.797 --> 23:20.533
- FUCK!
THEY TOLD YOU, DIDN'T THEY?

23:20.567 --> 23:24.203
THEY COULDN'T WAIT.
- TOLD ME WHAT?

23:24.236 --> 23:27.574
- WHAT ARE YOU TALKING ABOUT?
- GAY PRIDE.

23:27.607 --> 23:29.776
WHAT ARE YOU TALKING ABOUT?

23:29.809 --> 23:31.678
- GAY PRIDE.
HOW DID THEY TURN OUT?

23:31.711 --> 23:33.646
- YOU'RE GOING TO HATE ME
FOR SAYING THIS,

23:33.680 --> 23:36.082
BUT YOU MAKE
ONE BITCHIN' BROAD.

23:36.115 --> 23:38.651
- I CAN'T BELIEVE I LET YOU
TALK ME INTO WEARING A DRESS.

23:38.685 --> 23:40.720
- [chuckles]

23:40.753 --> 23:43.623
- HERE I AM, KISSING MY BOSS,

23:43.656 --> 23:44.824
THE BIGGEST ASSHOLE
IN THE WORLD.

23:44.857 --> 23:47.727
- HONEY, THAT'S WHAT PRIDE
IS ALL ABOUT.

23:47.760 --> 23:51.564
LOVE AND FORGIVENESS, I MEAN.

23:51.598 --> 23:53.900
ARE YOU WEARING BLUSH?

24:06.679 --> 24:08.615
- [sighs]

25:14.180 --> 25:16.783
- THE LOST BOY RETURNS.

25:23.022 --> 25:24.791
[refrigerator door shuts]

25:24.824 --> 25:26.092
[bottle cap clicks off]

25:32.298 --> 25:34.967
- [chuckling]

25:36.168 --> 25:38.705
[bottle clatters]

25:40.740 --> 25:41.974
- FEELING BETTER?

25:42.008 --> 25:44.911
- LOTS.

25:44.944 --> 25:46.779
- HOW'S DAPHNE?

25:46.813 --> 25:49.315
- SHE AND HER ROOMMATES
HAD TO STUDY.

25:49.348 --> 25:51.918
FORTUNATELY,
THAT'S NOT MY PROBLEM.

25:51.951 --> 25:54.721
I WENT TO WOODY'S.
I LET GUYS BUY ME DRINKS.

25:54.754 --> 25:56.589
THEY ALL WANTED TO FUCK ME.

25:56.623 --> 25:59.659
AT LEAST I STILL HAVE MY LOOKS.

25:59.692 --> 26:00.693
I TOLD THEM NO.

26:00.727 --> 26:03.562
I'M SAVING THAT FOR YOU.

26:06.699 --> 26:08.801
- AREN'T YOU A SWEETHEART?

26:08.835 --> 26:11.671
- LET'S GO.
COME ON.

26:11.704 --> 26:13.172
- LATER.

26:13.205 --> 26:15.708
COME AND SEE WHAT I GOT YOU.
- WHAT?

26:15.742 --> 26:17.209
A NEW BUTT PLUG?
MANACLES?

26:17.243 --> 26:19.211
I KNOW, A VACU-PUMP?
- BETTER.

26:19.245 --> 26:21.614
I SAW IT TODAY AT WORK. IT'S--
- I'M NOT INTERESTED.

26:21.648 --> 26:22.815
- YOU DON'T EVEN KNOW
WHAT IT IS.

26:22.849 --> 26:24.617
- SURE I DO.
IT'S FALSE HOPE.

26:24.651 --> 26:26.686
- BUT YOU CAN DRAW WITH IT, SEE?

26:26.719 --> 26:27.920
SAME AS A PEN

26:27.954 --> 26:29.288
OR A PENCIL
OR A PAINTBRUSH.

26:29.321 --> 26:31.090
JUST MUCH EASIER TO CONTROL.

26:31.123 --> 26:35.628
- OH, LIKE WITH MY GIMP HAND?

26:35.662 --> 26:38.097
- AND THERE'S A MILLION SPECIAL
EFFECTS YOU CAN CREATE WITH IT.

26:38.130 --> 26:40.967
STOP BEING A FUCKING PRINCESS
AND COME GIVE IT A TRY.

26:41.000 --> 26:43.369
- WHAT FOR?
TO MAKE YOU HAPPY?

26:43.402 --> 26:45.104
SO THAT YOU CAN TELL YOURSELF

26:45.137 --> 26:46.706
YOU FIXED
LITTLE JUSTIN'S PROBLEMS

26:46.739 --> 26:49.842
AND MADE EVERYTHING ALL BETTER?

26:49.876 --> 26:51.644
WELL, YOU CAN'T FIX THIS,
ALL RIGHT?

26:51.678 --> 26:53.612
NO ONE CAN.

26:57.750 --> 26:58.885
- SO YOU'RE JUST GOING TO QUIT.

26:58.918 --> 27:01.821
- IT'S OVER, ALL RIGHT?

27:01.854 --> 27:03.890
ACCEPT IT.
I'M NOT GOING TO DRAW AGAIN.

27:03.923 --> 27:06.659
AND NO FUCKING
ELECTRONIC CRAYOLA BOX

27:06.693 --> 27:08.895
IS GOING TO FIX THAT.

27:13.032 --> 27:15.301
SO WHY DON'T YOU COME FUCK ME
BEFORE I PASS OUT?

27:22.909 --> 27:24.210
- EXCUSE ME, SIR,
CAN YOU TELL ME

27:24.243 --> 27:25.712
WHERE I CAN FIND
THE RUBBER NOSES?

27:25.745 --> 27:27.780
I HEAR THEY'RE GETTING YOU
A BUNNY SUIT

27:27.814 --> 27:29.315
FOR THE EASTER SALE.

27:29.348 --> 27:31.050
- DON'T YOU GUYS HAVE
ANYTHING BETTER TO DO,

27:31.083 --> 27:33.753
LIKE YOUR JOBS?
- WE'RE JUST KIDDING AROUND.

27:33.786 --> 27:35.988
- WELL, WHY DON'T YOU KID AROUND
SOMEWHERE ELSE?

27:36.022 --> 27:38.190
[laughter]

27:38.224 --> 27:41.327
THEY'RE THE CLOWNS.

27:41.360 --> 27:44.697
- THEY WERE RIGHT.
I WAS RIDICULOUS.

27:44.731 --> 27:47.834
- OKAY, NOVOTNY,
BETTER GET INTO THIS.

27:47.867 --> 27:49.368
- WHAT?

27:49.401 --> 27:51.070
- YOU DID SUCH A GREAT JOB
YESTERDAY,

27:51.103 --> 27:52.138
I FIGURED
YOU SHOULD DO IT AGAIN TODAY.

27:52.171 --> 27:54.907
- NO FUCKING WAY!
- HEY, WATCH YOUR LANGUAGE, PAL.

27:54.941 --> 27:57.409
THIS IS A FAMILY STORE.
NOW GET DRESSED.

27:57.443 --> 27:59.178
- SORRY, ANDREW,
YOU'RE JUST GOING TO HAVE

27:59.211 --> 28:00.179
TO FIND SOMEBODY ELSE.

28:00.212 --> 28:03.182
- EXCUSE ME?
- I SAID NO!

28:03.215 --> 28:05.084
- IN CASE YOU'VE FORGOTTEN,
I'M THE MANAGER NOW.

28:05.117 --> 28:06.986
- I'M WELL AWARE OF THAT,

28:07.019 --> 28:09.121
SINCE YOU'VE MANAGED
TO NEVER LET ME FORGET IT.

28:09.155 --> 28:11.190
BUT THE THING YOU CAN'T FORGET

28:11.223 --> 28:13.025
IS THAT THE ONLY REASON
YOU HAVE THIS JOB

28:13.059 --> 28:14.360
IS BECAUSE I LEFT.

28:14.393 --> 28:17.196
MY ONLY MISTAKE IS
I NEVER SHOULD HAVE COME BACK.

28:17.229 --> 28:21.200
- I SAID PUT IT ON.

28:21.233 --> 28:23.702
- AND I SAID NO.

28:27.106 --> 28:29.475
- PUT IT ON...

28:29.508 --> 28:31.978
OR YOU'RE FIRED.

28:41.020 --> 28:43.255
- FUCK YOU.

28:46.192 --> 28:49.996
BYE, TRACE.
- BYE.

28:51.864 --> 28:54.834
- SO LONG, LOVER-BOY.

28:57.003 --> 28:59.471
- ATTENTION, BIG Q SHOPPERS,

28:59.505 --> 29:02.875
ANOTHER DAY,
ANOTHER DOLLAR SALE.

29:02.909 --> 29:04.977
FOR ALL YOUR COSMETIC NEEDS,

29:05.011 --> 29:06.913
FROM LIPSTICK TO EYELINER...

29:06.946 --> 29:10.082
- YEAH!

29:10.116 --> 29:12.318
- WATCH YOUR BACKS,
HOT STUFF COMING THROUGH.

29:12.351 --> 29:14.854
- NO KIDDIN'.
WHOO!

29:14.887 --> 29:17.256
- I'VE NEVER SEEN ANYONE EAT
A DOUGHNUT LIKE THAT BEFORE.

29:17.289 --> 29:19.091
IS IT A SOUTHERN SORT OF THING?

29:19.125 --> 29:22.328
- MM, MORE OF A SURVIVAL SORT
OF THING.

29:22.361 --> 29:26.132
TRY AND GRAB IT.

29:26.165 --> 29:30.236
- OH, GOD!
[chuckles]

29:30.269 --> 29:31.437
- MISS MANNERS
MAY NOT HAVE APPROVED,

29:31.470 --> 29:33.372
BUT, WITH SIX HUNGRY BROTHERS
AND SISTERS,

29:33.405 --> 29:35.141
IT'S HOW I KEPT MY BELLY FULL.

29:35.174 --> 29:39.511
[tapping cup]
MM, HEY! MORE COFFEE, JAVA BOY.

29:49.255 --> 29:51.457
- OH!
- CAREFUL. CAREFUL.

29:53.325 --> 29:55.494
- MAYBE YOU OUGHT TO GIVE
YOUR HAND A REST, HUH, SUNSHINE?

29:55.527 --> 29:57.964
- MAYBE YOU SHOULD MIND
YOUR OWN FUCKING BUSINESS.

30:02.101 --> 30:03.202
- WHAT'D YOU JUST SAY TO ME?

30:03.235 --> 30:04.904
- I SAID MIND YOUR OWN BUSINESS.

30:04.937 --> 30:06.438
- YEAH, I HEARD WHAT YOU SAID.

30:06.472 --> 30:08.107
- THEN WHY'D YOU ASK ME
TO REPEAT IT?

30:08.140 --> 30:09.575
- I WANTED TO BE SURE
I HEARD IT CORRECTLY.

30:09.608 --> 30:12.344
- [sighs]
LEAVE ME THE FUCK ALONE.

30:14.480 --> 30:17.183
- JUSTIN!

30:20.552 --> 30:23.089
I KNOW WHAT HAPPENED
TO YOU SUCKS,

30:23.122 --> 30:26.158
AND I'M NOT GONNA GIVE YOU
SOME POLLYANNA SHIT

30:26.192 --> 30:28.060
ABOUT EVERYTHING HAPPENS
FOR A REASON

30:28.094 --> 30:31.463
OR THIS WAS GOD'S GIFT
TO MAKE YOU STRONG.

30:31.497 --> 30:34.066
'CAUSE, IF ANYBODY HAD SAID THAT
TO ME, HONEY,

30:34.100 --> 30:35.601
WHEN VIC WAS DYING,
I WOULDA PUNCHED 'EM

30:35.634 --> 30:40.539
RIGHT IN THE FUCKING MOUTH.

30:40.572 --> 30:43.509
ALL YOU CAN DO AT A TIME
LIKE THIS

30:43.542 --> 30:47.880
IS JUST HANG ON
UNTIL THE SCENERY CHANGES.

30:50.516 --> 30:54.620
SO WHY DON'T YOU JUST LET ME
LEND A HAND

30:54.653 --> 30:56.588
IN POURING THE HOT STUFF, OKAY?

31:00.692 --> 31:02.929
- MM-HMM.

31:04.330 --> 31:07.499
- AND ONE MORE THING.

31:07.533 --> 31:10.436
THE NEXT TIME YOU TALK TO ME
LIKE THAT,

31:10.469 --> 31:12.304
I'M GONNA RIP YOU
A NEW BUTTHOLE SO BIG,

31:12.338 --> 31:16.608
YOU'RE GONNA BE ABLE
TO TAKE A CANNON UP YOUR ASS.

31:16.642 --> 31:18.510
[knocking on counter]

31:18.544 --> 31:20.646
- BYE.
- BYE.

31:20.679 --> 31:22.348
- CAN I GET SOME EGGS EASY OVER
WITH BROWN TOAST?

31:22.381 --> 31:27.586
- SOMETHING TELLS ME
YOU NEED A BREAK.

31:27.619 --> 31:30.556
[indistinct chatter]

31:35.561 --> 31:37.463
SO WHAT DO YOU THINK?

31:37.496 --> 31:41.033
- WHO GIVES A SHIT WHAT I THINK?

31:41.067 --> 31:44.336
[clears throat]
THE COMPOSITION'S GOOD.

31:44.370 --> 31:49.008
THE TECHNIQUE, USE OF COLOR,
IT'S INTERESTING.

31:49.041 --> 31:51.077
I DON'T PARTICULARLY CARE
FOR THE SUBJECT MATTER.

31:51.110 --> 31:53.112
- A SAD YOUNG MAN.

31:53.145 --> 31:54.413
- YEAH, WHO NEEDS
TO LOOK AT THAT?

31:54.446 --> 31:59.618
- ESPECIALLY WHEN YOU'VE GOT
A MIRROR.

31:59.651 --> 32:01.153
- I LIKE THAT ONE.

32:01.187 --> 32:03.089
IT'S, UM...

32:03.122 --> 32:05.357
IT'S LESS REPRESENTATIONAL.
IT'S MORE SPONTANEOUS.

32:05.391 --> 32:07.526
IT'S MORE ANGRY.

32:07.559 --> 32:10.462
- LIKE WHAT YOU'RE FEELING?

